Joe was finishing his last
year at West Point when

00:06:43.010 --> 00:06:45.160
Flight 11 crashed
into the North Tower,

00:06:45.160 --> 00:06:49.400
killing his brother James, who
worked at Cantor Fitzgerald.

00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:54.080
And prior to working with
Team Red, White &amp; Blue,

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:57.390
he was an associate at the
Combating Terrorism Center,

00:06:57.390 --> 00:07:01.240
an instructor in the Department
of Social Sciences at the US

00:07:01.240 --> 00:07:03.580
Military Academy at West Point.

00:07:03.580 --> 00:07:06.770
He also worked in Afghanistan
in counterinsurgency work.

00:07:06.770 --> 00:07:10.540
He spent six years in the
Army, two deployments in Iraq,

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:13.741
and received his Master's
degree in Public Policy

00:07:13.741 --> 00:07:14.740
from the Kennedy School.

00:07:18.348 --> 00:07:20.840
Lieutenant Colonel Eric
Dill, US Marine Corps.

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:22.680
Happy birthday, sir.

00:07:22.680 --> 00:07:25.660
For those who don't know, today
is-- where are the Marines?

00:07:25.660 --> 00:07:26.160
Excellent.

00:07:30.190 --> 00:07:32.120
Lieutenant Colonel
Dill was conducting

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:34.620
training in Australia on 9/11.

00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:36.390
His unit immediately
deployed to prepare

00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:38.894
for the invasion of Afghanistan.

00:07:38.894 --> 00:07:40.810
They were part of the
first conventional force

00:07:40.810 --> 00:07:44.720
to enter the country, seizing
Kandahar International Airport.

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:47.480
He began his military career
enlisting in the Marine Corps

00:07:47.480 --> 00:07:52.770
in February of 1993,
attended Texas Tech,

00:07:52.770 --> 00:07:55.910
went on to be commissioned
as a Second Lieutenant,

00:07:55.910 --> 00:07:58.447
and had multiple,
multiple assignments.

00:07:58.447 --> 00:08:00.030
His service included
three deployments

00:08:00.030 --> 00:08:02.150
to Iraq, two deployments
to Afghanistan,

00:08:02.150 --> 00:08:03.635
multiple deployments to Africa.

00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:11.340
Mr. Mark Nutch.

00:08:11.340 --> 00:08:13.780
Mark Nutch is a US
Army Special Forces

00:08:13.780 --> 00:08:15.760
veteran from
Leavenworth, Kansas.

00:08:15.760 --> 00:08:19.520
Thanks for making
the trip here today.

